"C:\Dev\matlab-functions\reports\phi1_from_pt_shape_test.md","46","PT-derived differential/curvature-weighted descriptors capture a nontrivial part of Phi1’s symmetry/curvature structure, but the best PT-only combination still falls short of the canonical Phi1 shape quality (especially in normalized RMSE and/or robustness). This supports a “partial geometric resemblance” view: Phi1’s shape partly tracks barrier/CDF operators, but not fully reducible to PT alone."
