"C:\Dev\matlab-functions\reports\phi1_instability_analysis.md","114","The instability comes from using a local Phi1 representation (coarse intersection grid + different normalization + partial T overlap) as if it were canonically equivalent. It is not shape-equivalent (cosine 0.696, explained variance 0.417), so when injected into reconstruction it systematically degrades RMSE. Regime effects (kappa2-linked) amplify the mismatch but are not the primary trigger; the trigger is pipeline non-equivalence plus normalization transfer failure."
